Exemple: How to capture and save 10 images:

    This exemple shows you how to make images with the tiff plugin used with the Xpad areaDetector driver for imxpad detector on the medm interface.


First of all you need to turn on the TIFF plugin . You can access it via the all menu for exemple (fig 1,2)

(fig1)

(fig 2)

Make sure you enable it (fig 3)

(fig 3)


The plugin is now running but as you can see most fields are empty and you have got to fill some for it to work. You can for instence enable autosave, specify a filename a filepath and a filname format, chose Write mode and else. Important fields are marked with a green pepper on fig 4 .

Moreover, The plugin doesn't know what sizes are going to be the images so once you know for sure what exposure parameters you want for you serie of images, do one blank acquisition for it to know the dimensions (dimensions can change from one set of parameters to another and you can also save this image in single mode). (fig 4->5)


(fig 4:filling fields and making a blank exposure)

 |

\/


(fig.5:dimensions are now known by the plugin)


Now you can start the capture from the plugin


and then launch the acquisition, here i will save the first 10 images of a 100 images exposure



now wait for  "Capturing"  to return to "Done" and you can use your images ! (on any 32bit Mono TIFF viewers)
